Canal Street, west side, from Watts Street, at the south end of Renwick, to Greenwich Street.
September 27, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, nearly four years later. The triangular building, 486-490 Canal Street (116-118 Watts Street) has been replaced by a filling station. Only its west wall has been preserved, as a protection to the frame buildings immediately behind.
June 30, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same at a later date. Note absence of former frame houses.
July 27, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
